    • Constructor Detail

      • OctNode

        public OctNode(short _codeR,
               short _codeS,
               short _codeT,
               byte _level)
        The position of the node in the tree is defined by its code (R, S, T coordinates) and its level. This is not the position is space (X, Y, Z coordinates) but the position in the data structure. At the level 3, there are 8x8x8 possible nodes, so the R, S, T coordinates can be an integer or a short between 0 and 7. Higher or lower integers are valid possible but will be out of bounds. Level can be between 0 and 127.

      • intersectPoint

        public OctRST intersectPoint(OctRST start,
                             OctRST direction,
                             float minDist,
                             float maxDist)
        ADAPTED FROM https://gist.github.com/aadnk/7123926.

        Calculates intersection with the given ray between a certain distance interval.

        Ray-box intersection is using IEEE numerical properties to ensure the test is both robust and efficient, as described in:
        Amy Williams, Steve Barrus, R. Keith Morley, and Peter Shirley: "An Efficient and Robust Ray-Box Intersection Algorithm" Journal of graphics tools, 10(1):49-54, 2005

      • volumeHexa

        public float volumeHexa(OctOctree _octree)
        Computes the volume of the node based on its 8 vertices, also valid if deformed. Based on "Efficient computation of volume of hexahedral cells", J. Grandy. http://www.osti.gov/scitech/servlets/purl/632793

      • isCodeWB

        public boolean isCodeWB(OctOctree _octree)
        Returns true if the node code is within the bounds of the octree. Returns false for nodes that have a negative or too large R, S or T code.

      • isLevelWB

        public boolean isLevelWB(OctOctree _octree)
        Returns true if the node level is within the current bounds of the octree (between min. and max. level).

      • isWB

        public boolean isWB(OctOctree _octree)
        Returns true if 'ifLevelWB' AND 'ifCodeWB' are true

      • isSelected

        Returns true if node is selected.

      • isChildOf

        public boolean isChildOf(OctNode _t)
        Returns true if the node is included in the '_t' node (check if the node is a child of _t). Is false if the two nodes have the same level or are equals.

      • isParentOf

        public boolean isParentOf(OctNode _t)
        Returns true if the node is a parent of '_t' (check if the node is a parent of _t). Is false if the two nodes have the same level.

      • isSiblingOf

        public boolean isSiblingOf(OctNode _t)
        Returns true if the node is a sibling of '_t' (check if the nodes have the same parent). Is false if the two nodes don't have the same level or are equals.

      • isNeighborOf

        public boolean isNeighborOf(OctNode _t)
        Returns true if the node is a neighbor of '_t'. Returns false if the node '_t' equals the node.
